    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0001",
      "text": "INCITS xxx-200x Link Services Rev 1.61 November 3, 2006",
      "bbox": [
        301.08,
        37.27,
        539.95,
        47.32
      ],
      "block_index": 1,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0002",
      "text": " 117",
      "bbox": [
        518.28,
        723.59,
        537.71,
        734.7
      ],
      "block_index": 2,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0003",
      "text": "4.2.44",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        57.65,
        123.76,
        68.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0004",
      "text": "Link Keep Alive (LKA)",
      "bbox": [
        133.83,
        57.65,
        238.2,
        68.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0005",
      "text": "4.2.44.1  Overview",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        82.97,
        182.15,
        94.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0006",
      "text": "The LKA ELS is used for traffic generation. It provides a means to generate traffic in order to confirm",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        106.97,
        540.04,
        118.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0007",
      "text": "that the link is still intact and/or to ensure the link is not terminated due to lack of traffic. The LKA ELS",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        118.97,
        540.04,
        130.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0008",
      "text": "was specifically designed to keep Fibre Channel backbone links alive (e.g., some TCP implementa-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        130.97,
        540.04,
        142.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0009",
      "text": "tions will disconnect connections that are not used for some time period).",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        142.96,
        418.06,
        154.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0010",
      "text": "The LKA ELS is sent by a VE_Port or B_Access portal to a remote peer in order to determine the",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        166.96,
        539.94,
        178.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0011",
      "text": "health of a link between them, or simply to generate traffic to keep a link from being terminated. Should",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        178.96,
        539.97,
        190.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0012",
      "text": "a link be comprised of more than one physical or virtual connection, the LKA may be transmitted on",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        190.96,
        540.0,
        202.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0013",
      "text": "each of the connections. If a connection is configured to handle only specific class(es) of traffic, the",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        202.96,
        539.96,
        214.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0014",
      "text": "LKA shall be sent on a class of service the connection is configured for.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        214.96,
        411.49,
        226.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0015",
      "text": "The LKA ELS request Sequence shall consist of a single frame requesting the recipient to reply using",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        238.96,
        539.9,
        250.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0016",
      "text": "the ACC reply Sequence consisting of a single frame. The LKA ELS request frame shall indicate",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        250.96,
        539.86,
        262.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0017",
      "text": "End_Sequence and Sequence Initiative transfer as well as other appropriate F_CTL bits as defined in",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        262.96,
        539.94,
        274.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0018",
      "text": "FC-FS-2. The LKA ELS shall be transmitted as a single frame Sequence and the ACC reply Sequence",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        274.96,
        540.02,
        286.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0019",
      "text": "is also a single frame Sequence. The LKA ELS shall be transmitted as an Exchange that is separate",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        286.96,
        540.04,
        298.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0020",
      "text": "from any other Exchange. The LKA ELS is applicable to Class F, 2, 3, and 4.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        298.96,
        434.82,
        310.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0021",
      "text": "The LKA ELS may be sent at any time. The LKA ELS should be sent at least every K_A_TOV if no",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        322.96,
        539.95,
        334.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0022",
      "text": "traffic has been sent and/or received on the connection. The default value for K_A_TOV shall be 1/2",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        334.96,
        539.98,
        346.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0023",
      "text": "E_D_TOV.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        346.96,
        144.3,
        358.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0024",
      "text": "If an accept is not received within E_D_TOV, a new LKA ELS may be transmitted in a new Exchange.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        370.96,
        540.08,
        382.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0025",
      "text": "The Exchange used for the previous LKA request shall be aborted.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        382.96,
        390.95,
        394.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0026",
      "text": "Upon discovering an error (e.g. due to service reject or failure to receive a timely accept in response",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        406.96,
        539.99,
        418.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0027",
      "text": "to one or more LKA ELS requests), the initiator shall initiate appropriate exception handling. The def-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        418.96,
        539.89,
        430.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0028",
      "text": "inition of appropriate exception handling is topology-specific. ",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        430.96,
        365.35,
        442.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0029",
      "text": "4.2.44.2  Protocol",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        454.96,
        178.28,
        466.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0030",
      "text": "a) Link Keep Alive request Sequence; and",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        478.96,
        297.42,
        490.08
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0031",
      "text": "b) LS_ACC or LS_RJT reply Sequence.",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        502.96,
        286.77,
        514.07
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0032",
      "text": "4.2.44.3  Request Sequence",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        526.96,
        227.12,
        538.07
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0033",
      "text": "Addressing: ",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        550.96,
        157.1,
        562.07
      ],
      "block_index": 15,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0034",
      "text": "The S_ID field shall be set to FFFFFDh, indicating the Fabric Controller of the VE_Port",
      "bbox": [
        157.08,
        550.96,
        540.14,
        562.07
      ],
      "block_index": 15,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 2
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0035",
      "text": "or B_Access portal originating the request. The D_ID field shall be set to FFFFFDh, indicating the Fab-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        562.96,
        540.03,
        574.07
      ],
      "block_index": 15,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0036",
      "text": "ric Controller of the remote peer.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        574.96,
        239.83,
        586.07
      ],
      "block_index": 15,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p136_s0037",
      "text": "Payload:",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        598.96,
        137.66,
        610.07
      ],
      "block_index": 16,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
